Privacy Policy for Gene Therapy Insights
Effective Date: 11/14/2024
1. Purpose
Gene Therapy Insights ("Service") is a tool designed to provide users with real-time insights into current research and clinical trials in gene therapy by accessing public sources like PubMed and ClinicalTrials.gov. This Service is intended for informational purposes only and is not a substitute for professional medical advice.
2. Data Collection
Gene Therapy Insights does not collect, store, or share any personal data. User interactions, including questions and queries, are processed solely within the real-time session and are not retained afterward. No user data is accessible to any party beyond the immediate session.
3. Third-Party Services
The Service retrieves data from third-party research databases (e.g., PubMed, ClinicalTrials.gov) to provide accurate and up-to-date information. Gene Therapy Insights does not store or share any identifiable information from these sources and adheres to these sources' privacy guidelines.
4. Data Security
As Gene Therapy Insights does not collect or retain any personal data, there is no risk of personal data exposure or breach. The Service operates in a secure environment to ensure safe handling of session-based interactions.
5. User Responsibility
Users are advised not to submit sensitive personal information, such as personal health or financial data, while using the Service. Gene Therapy Insights is designed for informational purposes only and should not be used to diagnose or treat any medical condition.
6. Contact Information
If you have questions or concerns about this privacy policy, please contact us at [joncasieri@gmail.com].
